Shell Scripting Setup Steps are as Follows :
1. First setup EC2 AWS instance name:linux-server, AMI:Ubuntu, Instance Type: T2 or T3micro, Security Group:allow SSh port(22)
   Cretae KeyPair: eg. server.pem

2. launch Instance

3. Now connect instance First open Gitbash in your laptop, and open that folder where your pem file is located eg. it is download folder so you have to write command in gitbash like
    cd Download then 
type ls check server.pem is downloaded. Then go to SSh block eg. copy {chmod 400 "server.pem"} This command without curly bracket and paste it into git bash

4. Then Copy Example command: ssh -i "server.pem" ubuntu@ec2-3-109-152-9.ap-south-1.compute.amazonaws.com 

5. now you can succesfully login in ubuntu using ssh

