Demo: vim hello.sh
In text editor vim we have to write shell script like:
click on I button open Insert mode
write script:
#!/bin/bash
echo "Teacher: Hello Student"
echo "Student: Hello Mam"
echo "Today we learn Shell Script"
echo "Ok MAm!!"
click on escape button
type-  :wq and enter

Now we have to check permission so type
ls -l hello.sh
so you get -rw-rw-r-- like wise so, you have to do execute permission

Type chmod 764 hello.sh {You give any of permission but execute permission is mandatory}
then again check ls-l hello.sh
so you get -rwxrw-r-- this permission

Now you can execute you shell script like:
./hello.sh 

so you will get 
Teacher: Hello Student
Student: Hello Mam
Teacher: Today we learn Shell Script
Student: Ok MAm!!




